<section containing-doc="D.C. Code" xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:codified="http://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="http://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify">
  <num>45-606</num>
  <heading>Oath to include affirmation.</heading>
  <text>Wherever an oath is required, an affirmation in judicial form, if made by a person conscientiously scrupulous about taking an oath, shall be deemed a sufficient compliance.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1189, ch. 854</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 49-206.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 49-206.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>